race.comment: Tricky. GOLD DECREE (7) has been building nicely in three runs to date, working home well at Wodonga for third despite going under as favourite. Handled the 1400m nicely there and should appreciate an extra 100m now. Drawn well, he can improve again and take this out. PARERA (2) has had plenty of chances but put in a good run last time at Mornington when sticking on well for second. This looks a winnable race and if he can land in a good spot he should go close again. HORATIUS (8) has been fair in two runs to date, getting back in the field each time and not beaten far last time at Mornington. Drawn to get back again but can improve and be hitting the line strongly. ASHINA (12) is a filly by Tivaci on debut for the Busuttin & Young stable. She'll likely get a lot more ground being a full sister to a St Leger winner but can run well. DOUBLET (6) next best.
